article.headline: Northeastern 88, New Hampshire 65
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Jose Juan Barea had 26 points and Marcus Barnes added 21 points as Northeastern beat New Hampshire 88-65 on Thursday night. After New Hampshire (8-18, 4-13) took an early 4-0 lead, Northeastern pulled away with first-half runs of 18-2 and 16-2 to take a 49-24 halftime lead. Northeastern (18-8, 14-3) which has won five straight games and eight of nine, would clinch the No. 2 seed in the America East tournament with a win over Albany on Sunday. Ben Sturgill had 14 points and Blagoj Janev had 13 to lead New Hampshire, which has lost six of its last seven. The Wildcats were outrebounded 40-29. Barnes had six 3-pointers and Barea had four as the Huskies tied a school record with 14 3-pointers. Northeatern hit 14 of 30 3-point attempts.
